When I work with Python NumPy, I often encounter use-cases
which require that I create a NumPy Array from lists.
%br/
%br/
The syntax below demonstrates creation of a simple Array from two lists which act as columns in the Array:

%pre
  %code.python
    import numpy as np
    list0 = [1.1, 2.2, 3.3]
    list1 = [11.1, 22.2, 33.3]
    myarray = np.array([list0, list1])
    print(myarray)

Another technique is to create an empty Array and then fill it with data from lists after I know what they are:

%pre
  %code.python
    import numpy as np
    list0 = [1.1, 2.2, 3.3]
    list1 = [11.1, 22.2, 33.3]
    number_of_rows    = len(list0)
    number_of_columns = 2
    myarray2 = np.zeros((number_of_rows, number_of_columns))
    myarray2[:,0] = list0
    myarray2[:,1] = list1
    print(myarray2)

